More than $ 440,000 has been raised for an Indiana pizzeria that said it would refuse to serve gay marriage ceremonies under new religious freedom laws after it was reportedly forced to close its doors .
Kevin O'Connor , who owns Memories Pizza in Walkerton , told reporters he has temporarily shut the restaurant 's doors after he received abusive phone calls and was trolled online .
A contributor from Glenn Beck 's The Blaze set up a fundraising page on GoFundMe for the pizzeria .
